Executive Profile
Scott M. Sperling  Executive Chairman, Federal Street Acquisition Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 24 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. Scott M. Sperling serves as a Co-President at Thomas H. Lee Partners, L.P. Mr. Sperling serves as the President of WMG Acquisition Corp. He serves as Co-President of Thomas H. Lee Equity Partners VI, L.P. He served as Managing Director of TH Lee Putnam Ventures. He joined Thomas H. Lee Partners in 1994 and served as its Managing Director. Prior to joining Thomas H. Lee, Mr. Sperling served for over 10 years the Managing Partner of the private capital affiliate of ... Harvard Management Company, where he started and led the private investment areas of the Harvard Endowment including buyouts, venture capital, real estate and commodities. Prior to that, he served as a Managing Partner of The Aeneas Group Inc. Before that, he was a Senior Consultant and case leader at the Boston Consulting Group and Designee of Thomas H. Lee Company. He served as Co-President of BT Triple Crown Merger Co., Inc. He was Managing Partner of Harvard Management Company, Inc. He serves as the Chairman of Citi Performing Arts Center. Mr. Sperling served as a Director of HM Publishing Corp. He has been a Director of CC Media Holdings, Inc. since May 2007. He serves as a Director of LiveWire Ventures LLC, Harvard Business School and Thermo Fisher Corp. He serves as Manager of iHeartMedia Capital I, LLC. He has been a Director of iHeartMedia, Inc. since May 2007 serves as its Co-Presiding Director. He has been a Director of The Madison Square Garden Company since September 30, 2015. He serves as a Director and is involved with a number of charitable and non-profit organizations. He has been the Executive Chairman of Federal Street Acquisition Corp since March 2017 and serves as its Director. He serves as the Chairman of the Brigham & Women's / Faulkner Hospital Group and Wang Theater. He serves as a Member of Harvard Business School Dean's Advisory Board and Harvard Business School's Rock Center for Entrepreneurship. He has been a Director of MSG Spinco, Inc. since September 11, 2015. He has been a Director of The Firm, Inc. since March 2004. He has been a Director of WMG Acquisition Corp. since March 04, 2004. He has been a Director of Houghton Mifflin Holdings Inc. since December 2002. He has been an Independent Director at Thermo Fisher Scientific, Inc. since November 2006. He serves as a Director of iHeartCommunications, Inc. Mr. Sperling serves as a Director of Partners HealthCare System, Inc. His current and prior Directorships also include Hawkeye Holdings, Front Line Management Companies Inc., Tibbar LLC, Wyndham Hotels and several other private companies. He served as a Director of Univision Communications Inc. until October 17, 2007, Pricellular Corp. since February 1996, Wind International, Inc. (Wyndham International Inc.) since June 1999, CTC Communications Group Inc. since May 2000, Beacon Properties Corporation since 1994 and eXcelon Corporation since 1988. Sperling served as a Director of Vertis Holdings, Inc. since December 1999. He served as a Director of MSG Networks Inc. from December 18, 2014 to September 30, 2015. He served as a Director of Fisher Scientific International Inc. since January 1998. He served as a Director of Spinnaker, GenTek Inc., The Learning Company, Experian Information Solutions and Livent Inc. He served as a Director of Broderbund LLC since February 1994 and ProcureNet Inc. since 1999. He served as a Director of Softkey International Inc. since February 1994 and Vertis, Inc. from May 2001 to October 2008. He served as a Member of Supervisory Board at ProSiebenSat.1 Media SE from May 18, 2004 to March 2007. He served as a Director of Pricellular Wireless Corp. He served as a Director of Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company since December 2002. He served as a Director of Warner Music Group Corp. since March 4, 2004. Mr. Sperling holds an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School and a B.S. degree from Purdue University.Read Full Background




